repository_summary: A PyTorch-based image classification project with data preprocessing, model training, and evaluation components

children.summary: Data loading and preprocessing utilities for image datasets

children.name: load_image_dataset
children.summary: Loads images from directory and creates PyTorch DataLoader with specified batch size and shuffling
children.docstring:
Load images from directory and create DataLoader.

Args:
    data_dir: Path to image directory
    batch_size: Number of images per batch
    shuffle: Whether to shuffle data

Returns:
    DataLoader object

children.name: preprocess_images
children.summary: Applies normalization and resizing transformations to images using ImageNet statistics
children.docstring: Preprocess images with normalization and resizing.

children.name: augment_images
children.summary: Applies data augmentation techniques including random rotation, flipping, cropping, and color jittering
Neural network architecture definitions using PyTorch including CNN layers and forward pass logic

children.name: ImageClassifier
children.summary: Convolutional neural network for image classification with residual connections and batch normalization

children.name: __init__
children.summary: Initializes model architecture with convolutional layers, pooling, batch normalization, dropout, and fully connected layers

children.name: forward
children.summary: Defines forward propagation through convolutional layers, pooling, and fully connected layers

children.name: get_feature_maps
children.summary: Extracts intermediate feature maps from specified layer for visualization and analysis
children.docstring: Extract feature maps from a specific layer.

children.name: initialize_weights
children.summary: Initializes model weights using Xavier or Kaiming initialization methods for better convergence
children.docstring: Initialize model weights with specified method.

children.summary: Training script with optimization loop, loss computation, gradient descent, and checkpoint saving

children.name: train_one_epoch
children.signature: def train_one_epoch(model, train_loader, optimizer, criterion, device, epoch_num)
children.summary: Trains model for one epoch by iterating through batches, computing loss, backpropagation, and updating weights

children.name: validate_model
children.summary: Evaluates model on validation dataset without gradient computation and returns loss and accuracy metrics

children.name: save_checkpoint
children.signature: def save_checkpoint(model, optimizer, epoch, loss, accuracy, save_path)
children.summary: Saves model checkpoint including state dict, optimizer state, epoch number, loss, and accuracy metrics

children.name: load_checkpoint
children.summary: Loads model checkpoint from disk and restores model weights and optimizer state for continued training
Evaluation utilities for computing accuracy, precision, recall, F1 score, and confusion matrix

children.name: calculate_accuracy
children.summary: Computes classification accuracy by comparing predicted labels with ground truth targets

children.name: compute_confusion_matrix
children.summary: Generates confusion matrix showing true vs predicted labels for multi-class classification

children.name: plot_training_curves
children.signature: def plot_training_curves(train_losses, val_losses, train_accs, val_accs, save_path)
children.summary: Creates matplotlib visualizations of training and validation loss and accuracy curves over epochs
Utility functions for logging, configuration management, device selection, and seed setting

children.name: setup_logger
children.summary: Configures Python logging with file and console handlers for training progress monitoring

children.name: set_random_seed
children.summary: Sets random seeds for Python, NumPy, and PyTorch to ensure reproducible results

children.name: get_device
children.summary: Detects and returns CUDA GPU device if available, otherwise returns CPU device for computation
